<p><b>Light</b> is an <a href="/wiki/Evocation" title="Evocation" class="mw-redirect">evocation</a> <a href="/wiki/Cantrip" title="Cantrip" class="mw-redirect">cantrip</a> available to <a href="/wiki/Bard" title="Bard">bards</a>, <a href="/wiki/Cleric" title="Cleric">clerics</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sorcerer" title="Sorcerer">sorcerers</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Wizard" title="Wizard">wizards</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-spellLists_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-spellLists-1">[2]</a></sup>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Description"> Description </span></h2>
<p>You use your action to touch an object no longer than 10 feet in any dimension, causing it to shine bright light of a color you choose in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. If the object is completely covered, the light is blocked. The <a href="/wiki/Spell" title="Spell" class="mw-redirect">spell</a> ends if you cast it again or dismiss the light as an action.
</p><p>If your target is an object held or worn by a hostile creature, the creature must pass a <a href="/wiki/Dexterity" title="Dexterity" class="mw-redirect">Dexterity</a> save to avoid being lit by the spell.<sup id="cite_ref-spellDesc_0-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-spellDesc-0">[1]</a></sup>
</p>
